{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595047","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595047"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15331"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15331","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15331"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0.04,0.08,0.04,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8022"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61096"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8022","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8022"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15331"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46543"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19492"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19494"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61096"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA liver biopsy specimen shows the following microscopic features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ELarge clear vacuoles within hepatocytes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ENeutrophilic inflammatory infiltrates\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHepatocyte ballooning\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EMallory-Denk bodies\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological diagnoses best describes these findings?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Steatohepatitis","Simple steatosis","Chronic viral hepatitis","Primary biliary cholangitis","Haemochromatosis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis liver biopsy shows classic features of \u003Cstrong\u003Esteatohepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E. The key diagnostic features include fat droplets (appearing as clear vacuoles), inflammatory infiltrates (particularly neutrophils), and hepatocyte ballooning. Mallory-Denk bodies (eosinophilic intracellular inclusions) are also characteristic.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESimple steatosis\u003C/strong\u003E shows only fat droplets without inflammation or ballooning. \u003Cstrong\u003EChronic viral hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows lymphocytic rather than neutrophilic inflammation with interface hepatitis. \u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary biliary cholangitis\u003C/strong\u003E shows bile duct destruction and granulomas. \u003Cstrong\u003EHaemochromatosis\u003C/strong\u003E shows brown pigment deposition within hepatocytes without significant inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Steatohepatitis shows characteristic histological features including fat droplets, inflammatory infiltrates, and hepatocyte ballooning.","Key histological features help distinguish steatohepatitis from simple steatosis."],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.00